description._content: Post Party Ms. Pac Man

Pint Glasses now available at www.upadowna.com/shop Stobist setup: Glass is on a white poster board sweep filled with Bass Pale Ale (Mmmm.) Quantaray QDC 900WA flash to camera left- level with glass. White printer paper was taped to the narrow edge of a cardboard box to create a reflector on camera right. Another box was set directly in between the flash and glass to prevent any direct light. The main light comes from the illuminated background while the narrow reflector provides the highlight strip to the right of the logo. Learn how to light at Strobist.

Pint Glasses now available at www.upadowna.com/shop Stobist setup: Glass is on a white poster board sweep filled with Guiness. Quantaray QDC 900WA flash to camera left- level with glass. White printer paper was taped to the narrow edge of a cardboard box to create a reflector on camera right. This setup was almost exactly the same as the Bass version, however the box blocking the flash was removed. Direct light was needed to illuminate the logo since Guiness is so dark that no light passes through to light the logo from behind. I also added a LumiQuest softbox to the flash to soften the main highlight. The narrow reflector provides the highlight strip to the right of the logo which is more evident on the darker beer. Learn how to light at Strobist.

description._content: This was a tricky shot. Done in a crowded machine shop with overhead fluorescents, daylight from windows and a tungsten shop lamp (on the right edge.) Strobist: Closed blinds, trying to block all daylight. 1 Vivitar 285, camera left, bounced into an umbrella with Full CTG (to balance Fluorescents) and 1/4 CTO (to warm it up slightly) Exposure was set for the tungsten lamp hitting the face and drill. The Flash was set to +1 stop. An assistant held a reflector ( camera right) to bounce the flash back into the hair. Learn how to light at Strobist. Learn how to camp and drink beer at UpaDowna

photo.title: UCCS - Wind Tunnel

description._content: This was a 1 light setup as my second Cactus V2 receiver crapped out the night before this shoot. That's the price you pay when you don't pay full price. This room was lit with fluorescents. The wind tunnel window was lit by an upside down fluorescent light table sitting on top. Strobist: Vivitar 285 bounced into an umbrella camera left. Gelled with a Full CTG and 1/4 CTO to balance fluorescent lights. Exposure set to balance flash and light table. Learn how to light at Strobist. Learn how to camp and drink beer at UpaDowna

photo.tags: college student teacher learning teaching professor uccs strobist

Assistant holding a reflector camera right to bounce light back into the instrument panel. The shutter was left open longer (don't remember how long) to expose the LCD numbers on the left.
